Some heavily armed men, believed to be kidnappers have abducted a police inspector and one other person in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Abuja. A resident of the community said the incident happened, on Sunday around 2:00 am at Rubochi community in Kuje Area Council. According to him, the gunmen invaded the community in their large numbers and whisked away the police inspector, Selven and Nengba Mundi. Budget Defence: Diaspora C’mttee expresses displeasure… Gbajabiamila mourns Jummai Balewa UNICEF, OYO SUBEB initiate actions on ECD Development in… Ghost workers: Bauchi govt sets up investigative committee ALSO READ: BREAKING: 228 prisoners escape, houses submerged as flood sacks Kogi community The kidnappers first abducted officer before proceeding to the house of the second victim. “They whisked away officer after he failed to surrender his rifle to them. They asked him to surrender the gun he used for patrol on Friday to them but he declined and said he had handed over the rifle at the police station after patrol.” He added. When contacted, the acting spokesperson for the FCT Police Command, Maryam Yusuf, an Assistant Superintendent of Police (ASP), said she was not aware of the latest kidnap incident, and promised to get back. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
